quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
37,127,"But they denounced him as a liar, so they will surely be arraigned (for punishment),"
37,128,"except Allah's chosen servants. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
from the punishment, who did not belie the Prophet Elijah
(peace be upon him), and whom Allah chose from among
the nation for His worship.
37,129,"We preserved a good name for him among posterity. {1}",footnotes:1:The treatment that the Israelites meted out to the Prophet Elijah (peace be upon him) in his life has been referred to above
37,130,"Peace be upon Elias. {1}",footnotes:1:The words in the original are: Salam-un ala El-ya-sin. Some commentators say that El-ya-sin is the other name of the Prophet Elias
37,131,"Thus do We reward the good-doers."
37,132,"He was one of Our believing servants."
37,133,"And Lot too was one of the Messengers."
37,134,"(Call to mind) when We delivered him and all his kinsfolk,"
37,135,"except for an old woman who was among those that stayed behind. {1}",footnotes:1:This implies the wife of the Prophet Lot (peace be upon him)
37,136,"Then We utterly destroyed the rest of them."
37,137,"You pass by their desolate habitations in the morning {1}",footnotes:1:The reference is to the mined habitations of the people of Lot by which the Quraishite merchants passed day and night during their trade journeys to Syria and Palestine. 1
37,138,"and at night. Do you still not understand?"
37,139,"And Jonah too was one of the Messengers. {1}",footnotes:1:This is the third place where the Prophet Jonah (peace be upon him) has been mentioned in the Quran. Before this he has already been mentioned in Surah Younus and Surah Al-Anbiya. (For reference
37,140,"Call to mind when he fled to the laden ship, {1}",footnotes:1:The word abaqa in Arabic is used for the flight and escape of a slave from his master’s house.
37,141,"cast lots, and was among the losers."
37,142,"Then a fish swallowed him, and he was blameworthy. {1}",footnotes:1:This is what one understands from a study of these sentences:
37,143,"Had he not been one of those who glorify Allah, {1}",footnotes:1:It has two meanings and both are implied: (1) That the Prophet Jonah (peace be upon him) was not of the people who are heedless of God
37,144,"he would certainly have remained in its belly till the Day of Resurrection. {1}",footnotes:1:This does not mean that the fish would have lived till Resurrection and the Prophet Jonah (peace be upon him) would have remained alive in its belly till then
37,145,"But We threw him on a wide bare tract of land while he was ill; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,146,"and caused a gourd tree {1} to grow over him,",footnotes:1:The Arabic word yaqteen applies to a tree which does not stand on a stem but grows and spreads like a creeper
37,147,"and We sent him forth to a nation of a hundred thousand or more, {1}",footnotes:1:The mention of a hundred thousand people or more does not mean that Allah had any doubt about their number
37,148,"and they believed. So We let them enjoy life for a while. {1}",footnotes:1:Some people have taken exception to what we have written concerning this story of the Prophet Jonah in our commentary of Surahs Younus and Al-Anbiya. It would therefore be proper that we should reproduce here the explanations given by the other commentators in this regard.
37,149,"So ask their opinion: {1} “(Are you convinced) that your Lord should have daughters and you should have sons? {2}",footnotes:1:Traditions show that in Arabia the tribes of Quraish
37,150,"Did We create the angels as females the while they witnessed?”"
37,151,"Behold, it is one of their fabrications that they say:"
37,152,"“Allah has begotten.” They are liars!"
37,153,"Did He choose daughters rather than sons?"
